The paper deals with image hashing, which is a problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel hashing method that uses adversarial autoencoders, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also focuses on efficiency and effectiveness, which are important considerations in information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) applications. Finally, the paper proposes a principled approach to learning discrete hash functions, which is a fundamental problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
